gate: DONE
closed: 2026-06-03
owner: Daniil (DaniilDerkach)
pr: https://github.com/CT-CROP/CROP-search-hono/pull/332
note: |
  Merged to dev (search-hono) as part of combined PR#332.
  MAR added to BRAND_REGISTRY + STATIC_CARRIED_WHITELIST (also hardened VNT/FRR/MCH).
  967 tests green. Denis reviewed + approved.
sprint: S06
track: A
task: A1
title: "feat(search): add Marcrest (MAR) to hono BRAND_REGISTRY and carried-brand whitelist"
repos: [crop-search-hono]
priority: high
refs:
  - meetup-02-06-26 (John: "we're waiting for Marcress to be wired in")
requires: [BUN_HONO_CLOUDRUN]

impact: |
  Marcrest is the last of 4 brands needed for V2. Without this task, hono returns 404
  for `/api/brand/marcrest/models` and the entire brand landing + diagrams route is dead
  for Marcrest. All other V2 brand work (A2, A3) is unblocked once this lands.

description: |
  `src/lib/vocabulary-cache.ts` `BRAND_REGISTRY` drives the carried-brand gate for the
  brand-hub, brand-taxonomy, and models-by-brand routes. Marcrest is absent from the
  registry; adding it unlocks the vocabulary-cache read path for all Marcrest models.

  STATIC_CARRIED_WHITELIST in vocabulary-cache.ts is the fallback when the DB
  `brand_vocabulary` table has no row for MAR. Add MAR to the whitelist too so
  cold-start before cache refresh still serves Marcrest.

scope:
  in:
    - `BRAND_REGISTRY`: add entry for Marcrest (code: MAR, canonicalName: "Marcrest",
      vocabulary: ["Marcrest", "MARCREST"], productLines: ["MARCREST"],
      querySynonyms: ["marcrest", "mar", "bale barron"])
    - `STATIC_CARRIED_WHITELIST` (or equivalent): add "MAR"
    - Unit test: `normaliseManufacturerToken("marcrest")` returns "MAR";
      `getBrandDisplayName("MAR")` returns "Marcrest"
    - Contract smoke: `GET /api/brand/marcrest/models` returns 200 or valid 404
      (not an uncaught exception) after cache refresh
  out:
    - DB schema changes
    - Marcrest data ingestion (Alex/Vova scope)
    - Changing the `is_carried` flag in DB (that is Vova's task for the
      brand_vocabulary table refresh)

invariants:
  - No hardcoded brand logic outside BRAND_REGISTRY
  - querySynonyms lowercase
  - productLines UPPERCASE to match models.product_line column convention
  - All new brand codes must follow the 3-char uppercase convention (MAR ✓)

acceptance:
  - `normaliseManufacturerToken("marcrest")` → "MAR" (unit test)
  - `getCarriedBrandCodes()` includes "MAR" whether DB load succeeds or falls back
  - POST /admin/cache/refresh → GET /api/brand/marcrest/models returns 200 (requires
    Marcrest rows in models/search_vocabulary — if data not yet in DB, 404 with
    `code: "NOT_FOUND"` is acceptable; error must NOT be 500)

dep: none
output: src/lib/vocabulary-cache.ts + unit test update
